## **14.6 - Verify .gitignore**

Make sure sensitive files won't be committed to Git.

### **Edit file: `.gitignore`**

1. Open `.gitignore`
2. **Verify** it contains these lines (should already exist):
```
# dependencies
/node_modules
/.pnp
.pnp.js

# testing
/coverage

# next.js
/.next/
/out/

# production
/build

# misc
.DS_Store
*.pem

# debug
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# local env files
.env*.local
.env.production

# vercel
.vercel

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts